The paper discusses inference in graphical models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of algebraic decision diagrams (ADDs) suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the quantization technique may also be relevant to data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the application of the proposed method to variable elimination and junction tree propagation suggests a potential connection to control systems (cs.SY).
